race.comment: Onto the Grey's race. CLOUDLAND (2) won this race last year as a $3 favourite. He's going well, beating the handy Lord Penman two back before trying hard at Randwick. No doubt a title defence would have been the plan for some time, he'll go close. STATUARIO (1) is back a long way in distance having run in the G3 Coongy Cup over 2000m last time. Not sure if he'll be sharp enough here but on ability he's just about got them covered. GETAFIX (5) hasn't fired in two runs back but his best form is certainly good enough if he can find it with McDonald on. BERKSHIRE SHADOW (4) is going okay for this, outclassed last time in a stronger race at Caulfield. Gets Zahra on from the inside gate which can see improvement.
